# What travels and what stays.
#
# The harness lifts and shifts, so the repository must not carry one machine's
# truth to another. Everything below is either generated from source, specific
# to the machine that produced it, or both. Nothing here is hand-written input.

# --- Layer 3: per-install bindings -------------------------------------------
# Generated by `harness install` and specific to one project + engine pairing.
# Regenerate with: ./harness install <project-root>
/tools/app-harness
/.app-harness/contract.json

# --- Layer 4a: local run evidence --------------------------------------------
# Receipts record one run on one machine. That is correct for a receipt and
# exactly why they are not source. Regenerate by re-running the analyzer.
/.app-harness/reviews/
/artifacts/easy-harness-demo/
/artifacts/readme-harness-review/
/harness-output/
/tmp/
/sprint-output/tmp/

# Note: artifacts/ftpo-build-cycle-0010/ is deliberately NOT ignored. The README
# cites its build-receipt.json and metrics.json as primary artifacts, so they are
# part of the shipped unit rather than incidental run output.

# --- Environments and caches -------------------------------------------------
# .venv is pinned to one interpreter on one OS and must never be shared.
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/

# --- Transient ---------------------------------------------------------------
*.tmp
*.orig
*.rej

# A staging copy of the tracked tree, exported for committing elsewhere. Ignored
# so it can never recursively include itself or be committed into this repo.
# Safe to delete once it has been moved out.
/_commit-ready/

# --- OS metadata -------------------------------------------------------------
# Also excluded by the installer's skill manifest; ignored here so it never
# reaches the index in the first place.
.DS_Store
._*
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
.localized
